<h4>Ideas for Improving the Magician Class</h4>

<p>... a work in progress...</p>

<p><b>Spells</b></p>
<ol>
  <li>Give us spells that can only be used if we don't have a pet.&nbsp; (Pet
    summon spells check for a pet at the end of channeling, why can't a DD do
    that?)&nbsp; Make such spells very near wizard level in terms of
    output.&nbsp; If you wish, make them buff us in a manner to prevent a pet
    summons within 30 seconds of their use:
    <br>
    <p><i>Nenelar's Geomantic Gale</i> - Level 65 - 1800 dmg, 400 mana, 5s cast,
    0 hold, resist magic, -100 resist adjustment, not useable if a pet is up.</li>
  <li>Add resist adjustments to mage damage spells in line with those of wizards
    and druids.&nbsp; We shouldn't get the -300 lures of a wizard, but we should
    have a -100 spell or two.&nbsp; Not even magician DOTs have -100
    adjustments!</li>
</ol>
<p><b>Pets</b></p>
<ol>
  <li>Change pet heals to remove curse counters.&nbsp; Players have a hard
    enough time keeping up with cursed party members.&nbsp; Give mage pet heals
    the power to remove not only poison, but curses as well.</li>
  <li>Change pets so that they do not push a mob.&nbsp;&nbsp; Pets are not used
    on many high end encounters as they tend to push a mob out of position.&nbsp; Especially in water.</li>
  <li>The &quot;fix&quot; to the haste cap on pets wasn't the whole story.&nbsp;
    Pets are still capped at a delay of 19.&nbsp; That means the epic pet
    doesn't benefit any more from Burnout IV or V ... or even the AA Frenzied
    Burnout's haste component than it does from Burnout III.</li>
  <li>Allow magicians to be able to travel with a pet while invisible.&nbsp; Why
    is it such a problem?&nbsp; What exploit is such a concern?</li>
</ol>
<p><b>AAXP</b></p>
<ol>
  <li>Revisit magician class-level AA.&nbsp; Very few of them are desirable.</li>
</ol>
